    "Results in this section captured participants' thoughts on which stage is suggested would chiefly benefit from AI automation (Q: Based on your experience as a systematic reviewer, which particular stage in the SR process do you think would be of the most benefit using an automation method or tool?).",
    "As seen in Fig. 9, 18 (30%) of the 60 respondents indicated that the title and abstract screening would benefit most from using AI.",
    "Although most respondents rated this stage as easy, they still recommend it as the most beneficial stage.",
    "This confirms that the screening phase is the most time-consuming stage in the process (Booth et al. 2016; Przybyła et al. 2018).",
    "Although there are existing methods, exploring this stage is still necessary for reviewers."
  ],
